bip39
------------------------------------------
This is a portable C++ implementation of BIP39. The goal of this project is to
provide a BIP39 implementation with minimal dependencies and to be compatiable
with the most number of platforms, including Arduino.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libbip39-devel-1.1.1-1bl1
  libbip39_1-1.1.1-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.35.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ciband/bip39

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ciband/bip39/archive/refs/tags/1.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bip39-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bip39-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bip39-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bip39-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbip39_1-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbip39-devel-1.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bip39)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bip39.README
  /usr/share/doc/bip39/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bip39/README.md

(libbip39_1)
  /usr/bin/cygbip39-1.dll

(libbip39-devel)
  /usr/include/bip39/bip39.h
  /usr/include/bip39/word_list.h
  /usr/lib/libbip39.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/bip39.pc

